               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411129-name-113" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-113" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-113" type="surname" value="DRUMMOND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-113" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>ALEXANDER DRUMMOND</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Hugh Johnson, of Bexley, in Kent—he has an office in Bush-lane. On the 29th of October I was with his cart in Bush-lane, and received a parcel containing these boots—the prisoner took them out of the cart about twenty yards from the office—I caught him about seven or eight yards off with them. <hi rend="smallCaps">ADAH SPAREY</hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable No</hi>. 406.) I took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. There was a large rocking-horse in the cart—Drummond asked me to help him shove it up, which I did—the boots fell down—I went round and picked them up, and Drummond said I was going to steal them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411129-name-114" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-114" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-114" type="surname" value="DRUMMOND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-114" type="given" value="ALEXANDER"></interp>ALEXANDER DRUMMOND</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. He told me he was not going to steal them—while he struggled with me one of them dropped from him—I saw him leap from the cart with a parcel under his arm, but I did not know what it was till I caught him—I did not ask him to help me with the rocking-horse or in any way.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character.</p>
